    <!-- Two -->
      <section id="two" class="wrapper style3 fade-up" style="background-color:#EB8A93;">
        <div class="inner">
          <h2>The Possibilities</h2>
          <div class="features">
            <section>
              <span class="icon major fa-user-secret"></span>
              <h3>Chat Privately and Anonymously (if you want to be anonymous)</h3>
              <p>Are you stressed, lonely, or just want someone to talk to? Do you have ideas, concerns, or fears that you want to express but don't feel comfortable sharing them openly? With Tartan Talk you can chat privately and anonymously about anything with professional or student counselors.</p>
            </section>
            <section>
              <span class="icon major fa-heart"></span>
              <h3>Become a Student Volunteer</h3>
              <p>There are many students on CMU's campus who are passionate about giving back to their community and helping their fellow students in times of need. If you are one of them, you can become a student counselor on Tartan Talk!</p>
            </section>
            <section>
              <span class="icon major fa-play"></span>
              <h3>Have memorable conversations</h3>
              <p>Peer and professional counselors are here to listen to you and give you whatever feedback you need. A chat on Tartan Talk is bound to be thoughtful, insightful, and memorable.</p>
            </section>
            <section>
              <span class="icon major fa fa-users"></span>
              <h3>Start a Conversation</h3>
              <p>Signup today with your andrew ID or andrew email. If you want to talk anonymously, counselors won't be able to know who you are. The system uses your andrew ID to verify that you're a CMU student. </p>
            </section>
